New Zealand goods and services tax (NZ GST) at 15% is applicable to cross-border remote services and intangibles supplied by non-resident suppliers to person resident in New Zealand unless the person is a GST-registered business. A supplier must treat the recipient as not being a registered person unless the recipient notifies the supplier that they are a registered person and provides their NZ GST registration number.
In this connection, please provide the NZ GST registration number of your entity. If otherwise, NZ GST at 15% may be chargeable on our supply to you.
If there is any change to your entity's NZ GST registration number or if your entity subsequently deregisters for GST in New Zealand, please inform us immediately.

You agree to allow Microsoft to transmit your PayPal payment instructions to PayPal for purchases directly to Microsoft or an identified payment recipient utilizing a Microsoft platform. If you have a PayPal balance, it will be used first. If your preferred or default funding source is declined or expired, your backup-funding source will be charged. You allow PayPal to share your PayPal transaction details with Microsoft. The sharing of PayPal transaction details enables Microsoft to know if your payment has been successful, to help fulfill your transaction and provide payment receipts as identified in PayPal's Privacy Policy. You instruct PayPal to treat payment requests sent by Microsoft as authorized by you per the PayPal User Agreement. If you pay in a currency that is not the primary currency of your PayPal Account, PayPal will convert the amount using our then current rate. You can cancel this authorization or change your preferred funding source at any time in your PayPal account. If you withdraw your consent to use PayPal on Microsoft, PayPal may inform Microsoft.
